British workers have seen their wages rise by the lowest level for four years, while the cost of living continues to soar.

Wages increased by just 0.4 per cent in the first three months of 2013, including a fall in March.

New figures showed the number of people out of work rose by 15,000 to 2.52 million. The rate of unemployment rose to 7.8 per cent.

